<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-01-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-01-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="831" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d831">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.20/2.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-01-10">
                                    <hi rend="italic">January 10, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>War Department thinks, on account of climate, at least four officers
                            necessary to rehabilitate border police. Has found four
                            ex-noncommissioned officers who are ready to undertake the work,
                            provided they receive from Liberian Government commissions as follows:
                            One major, one captain, two lieutenants, with salaries respectively of
                            $2,500, $2,000, and $1,600 with housing. This must be definitely settled
                            before their departure. Cable decision Government.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>